data.name: sinceAddedCheckBoxLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
Usually "Plays per day" means the average number of times you played track since it was added to the library and till the day it was last played. So if you played track frequently in past and didn't play it for a long time then it will have high "Plays per day" value.
Sometimes it's better to use this option which will treat "Plays per day" as average number of times track was played since it was added to the library till today (no matter when it was last played).
It's recommended to "Auto rate on startup" your tracks if you want to use this option because "Plays per days in library" value depends on "today" date which is dynamic value and auto rating should change every day for each track in this case.
